<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>I joined a band 3 months before I left Chicago. My buddy, Charles, asked me if I'd be down to learn and record live performances of four songs with us and his two friends, Joe and James.</p>

<p>Of course, I get to join a fun band with great musicians and even better dudes that practices 5 minutes from where I live 3 months before I have to leave the city. :( :( :(</p>

<p>Two of the songs ("Lollicops" and "Pastoral Scene") were written by Brock Winthrop aka Alex Nichols (E1, Chapo). One, "Let's Start a War" is written by Charles Austin (E1, Solipse), who has a new album out TKINSERT HERE along with a funny music video TKINSERT. The other song is a cover by the band Asian Kung-Fu Generation.</p>

<p>I have a hard time picking a favorite: the brave political anthem ("Let's Start a War")? The deconstructed Sabbath of "Lollicops"? The hypermelodic janglepop of "Pastoral Scene"? Or the melodic joint-fitting of Asian Kung-Fu Generation</p>

